Sentencas: Nd1.93Sr0.07CuO4 nanofibers are prepared by electrospinning technique followed by a simple thermal treatment.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Nd1.93Sr0.07CuO4 nanofiber as cathode material for SOFC

Sentencas: The morphology and phase evolution of as-obtained fibers are characterized by TG-DTA, XRD, FT-IR and SEM, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Nd1.93Sr0.07CuO4 nanofiber as cathode material for SOFC

Sentencas: Typical ceramic fiber diameter is 100-200 nm, with length exceeding tens of microns.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Nd1.93Sr0.07CuO4 nanofiber as cathode material for SOFC

Sentencas: Rapid heating the nanofiber cathode at 1000 degrees C for 15 min results in homogeneous porous microstructure and good contact with the CGO electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Nd1.93Sr0.07CuO4 nanofiber as cathode material for SOFC

Sentencas: EIS analysis of the nanofiber electrode gives a polarization resistance of 0.26 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air, two times smaller than that from the powder cathode with the same composition.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Nd1.93Sr0.07CuO4 nanofiber as cathode material for SOFC

Sentencas: The excellent electrochemical performance can be attributed to the well constructed microstructure of the fiber cathode, which can promote surface oxygen diffusion or adsorption processes on the cathode.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Nd1.93Sr0.07CuO4 nanofiber as cathode material for SOFC
